condition.narrative: CLM shall no later than four (4) months after the Effective Date recruit an assistant accountant with qualifications acceptable tothe Association. CLM shall maintain, at all times during the implementation of the Project, with a composition, mandate, andresources satisfactory to the Association, the Cellule de Lutte contre la Malnutrition or CLM. CLM shall be responsible for theimplementation of Part 1 of the Project. Refer Section I of Schedule 2 to the Financing Agreement (FA).

No later than four (4) months after the Effective Date, the Recipient shall establish and thereafter maintain, at all times duringthe implementation of the Project, a Project steering committee with a composition, mandate, and resources satisfactory to theAssociation (“Project Steering Committee” or “PSC”). The PSC shall meet semi-annually. No later than four (4) months after theEffective Date, the Recipient shall establish and thereafter maintain the Project’s technical working Group (“Technical WorkingGroup”) which shall be chaired by the secretary general of MBGPE or any representative of the minister of MBGPE.Refer Section I ofSchedule 2 to the Financing Agreement (FA).

The PIU shall no later than four (4) months after the Effective Date: (A) recruit and thereafter retain at all times during theimplementation of the Project the following staff, inter alia, each with terms of reference, qualifications and experiencesatisfactory to the Association: (i) a communications officer, (ii) a child development technical officer, (iii) an internalauditor, (iv) an accountant and (v) a safeguards specialist, all with qualifications acceptable to the Association; (B) set up anadequate accounting and reporting system and (C) hire an external auditor for the Project. Refer Section I of Schedule 2 to theFinancing Agreement (FA).

The Recipient shall monitor and evaluate the progress of the Project and prepare Project Reports in accordance with the provisionsof Section 5.08 of the General Conditions. Each Project Report shall cover the period of one calendar semester, and shall befurnished to the Association not later than forty-five 45) days after the end of the period covered by such report. The Recipientshall have the Financial Statements audited in accordance with the provisions of Section 5.09(b) of the General Conditions. Eachaudit of the Financial Statements shall cover the period of one (1) fiscal year of the Recipient, commencing with the fiscal yearin which the first withdrawal is made. The audited Financial Statements for each such period shall be furnished to the Associationnot later than six (6) months after the end of such period. Refer Section II of Schedule 2 to the Financing Agreement (FA).
